{{Short description|Religious honorific in Islam}}
{{unreferenced|date=October 2015}}
{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2014}}
{{Usul al-fiqh}}
'''Allamah''' ({{lang-ar|علامه}}, [[Urdu]] and {{Lang-fa|{{nq|علامه}}}}), also spelled ''Allamah'' and ''Allama'', is an honorary title carried by scholars of Islamic [[fiqh]] (jurisprudence) and philosophy.

It is used as an honorific in [[Sunni Islam]] as well as in [[Shia Islam]], mostly in [[South Asia]], [[Middle East]] and [[Iran]]. Sunnis and Shias who have achieved the rank of a scholarship in several disciplines are often referred to by the title.

