'''Quecholli''' is the name of the fourteenth  month of the [[Aztec calendar]]. It is also a festival  in the [[Aztec religion]]  and the Principal deity is [[Mixcoatl]].It is called the Precious Feather and hunting is done during this season. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.wdl.org/en/item/6714/ | title=Quecholli, the 14th Month of the Aztec Solar Calendar | publisher=World Digital Library | accessdate=21 July 2013}}</ref><ref name="Conan2007" /><ref name="Gallatin1845">{{cite book|author=Albert Gallatin|title=Semi-civilized Nations of Mexico, Yucatan, A. Central America|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rvRRAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA83|accessdate=21 July 2013|year=1845|pages=83–}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.amoxtli.org/cuezali/festivals.html | title=The Aztec Festivals | publisher=www.amoxtli.org | accessdate=24 July 2013 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150916191933/http://www.amoxtli.org/cuezali/festivals.html | archivedate=16 September 2015 | df= }}</ref><ref name="Conan2007">{{cite book|author=Michel Conan|title=Sacred Gardens And Landscapes: Ritual And Agency|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=muhAPvjxXnQC&pg=PP84|accessdate=24 July 2013|year=2007|publisher=Dumbarton Oaks|isbn=978-0-88402-305-0|pages=84–}}</ref>

